owl:Class.rdfs:label: Categoria
Category
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class is used to group all domain categories and other domain concepts.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Classification scheme
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class groups all classifications schemes from AGROVOC (e.g. the AGRIS/CARIS Classification scheme.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Lexicalization
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class is used to store all lexicalization of all languges for AGROVOC. All terms (descriptors and non-descriptors) are here created as instances.
This class is used to store all lexicalization of type NOUN of all languges for AGROVOC. All terms (descriptors and non-descriptors) are here created as instances.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Nom
Nome
Noun

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This is used for all AGROVOC concepts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Concetti di dominio
Domain concept

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class is used to group all characteristics of concepts, such as definitions, images, etc.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Entity annotation

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has part
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <hasPart> Y. A composite entity X that can be identified as composed by one or more parts, between which Y. Use this relationship when none of the other partitivity relations (<component>, <composedOf>, <portion>, <member>, <includesSubprocess>) apply. E.g. in a plant ontology: {Taxonomic} <hasPart> {PartPlant};

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has component
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <hasComponent> X. An object X that is a part of a whole Y and has also an existence independently from Y. E.g. "engine" <hasComponent> "engine part"; "tree" <hasComponent> "leaf"; "cell" <hasComponent> "chromosome"; but NOT "blood" <hasComponent> "blood cell" (see <composedOf>).

Y <isAGrowthEnvironmentFor> X. An environment Y favorable to a taxon X. This is used as the inverse relationship of <growsIn>. Use this in a plant and related domain (e.g. fungi). E.g. "isarn region" <isAGrowthEnvironmentFor> "jasmine rice"; "moist soil" <isAGrowthEnvironmentFor> "rice";
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is a growth environment for

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <spatiallyIncludes> Y. Part X is an inalienable part of Y (the spatial region occupied by Y is a part of the spatial region occupied by X). E.g. "Africa" <spatiallyIncludes> "Congo"; "Asia" <spatiallyIncludes> "Southeast Asia"; "arm" <spatiallyIncludes> "hand".
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Spatially includes

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link Species to Subspecies.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Species includes Subspecies

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <isPartOf> X. A part Y that compose an entity X. Use this relationship when none of the other partitivity relations (<component>, <composedOf>, <portion>, <member>, <includesSubprocess>) apply. E.g. in a plant ontology: {PlantPart} <isPartOf> {Taxonomic};
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is part of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: to map domain concepts to any category in a classification scheme.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has mapped domain concept
Genus has family
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link genus to Family.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Compose
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <compose> X. A relation in which X composed of Y holds is one where Y consists of the material or substance of which X is made. This relation also subsumes <ingredientOf> and <substanceOf> relations. E.g. "blood gas", "blood lipid", "blood protein", "blood cell" <composes> "blood"; "water", "yeast" <compose> "beer".

X <isComposedOf> Y. A relation in which X composed of Y holds is one where Y consists of the material or substance of which X is made. This relation also subsumes <ingredientOf> and <substanceOf> relations. E.g. "blood" <composedOf> "blood cell", ""blood gas", "blood lipid", "blood protein"; "beer" <composedOf> "water", "yeast", (and by inheritance "hops" c.f. <madeFrom>).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is composed of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <isMemberOf> Y. A social or political unit (group or individual) X belongs to a social or political group Y. E.g. "cow" <isMemberOf> "herd"; "Algeria", "Benin", "Burkina Faso", etc. <isMemberOf> "Francophone Africa".
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is member of

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <isUseOf> X. {Use} Y <isUseOf> {Taxon} X. Use this in a plant domain. - {use} Y <isUseOf> {chemical substance} X. Use this for chemical substance. E.g.: "fruit" <isUseOf> "apple"; "cleaner" <isUseOf> "alcohol"; "pesticide" <isUseOf> "ddt";
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is use of
Order has class
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link order to class.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is term referenced in scope note
Is object of activity
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: From CWR ontology.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Uses process
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <usesProcess> X. One or more actions, activities, methods X that produce a change or development Y. E.g.: "fruit cleaning" <usesProcess> "sterilization".

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Grows in
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <growsIn> Y. A taxon X grows in an environment Y. Use this in a plant and related domain (e.g. fungi). E.g. "jasmine rice" <growsIn> "isarn region"; "rice" <growsIn> "moist soil";

Y <isUsedToMake> X. A substance or a product Y from which a product X can be mainly (in terms of importance) obtained. E.g. "cow milk" <isUsedToMake> "cheddar cheese"; "hops" <isUsedToMake> "beer" (see <composedOf>);
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is used to make
Is affected by
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <isAffectedBy> X. An object Y changes state or location because of an action of an agent X. E.g. "bacteria" <isAffectedBy> "sterilization"; "pest" <isAffectedBy> "pest control"; "agriculture" <isAffectedBy> "pollution of agriculture";

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Family includes genus
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link family to genus.

Y <isSourceOf> X. A source Y from which a substance or product X can be exclusively obtained, without any additional substance or product. E.g. "cow" <isSourceOf> "cow milk"; "plant" <isSourceOf> "plant oil"; "olive tree" <isSourceOf> "olive wood"; "chicken" <isSourceOf> "chicken meat"; but NOT "hops" <isSourceOf> "beer" (see <usedToMake>);
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is source of
Is made from
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <isMadeFrom> Y. A product X obtained mainly (in terms of importance) from a substance or a product Y. E.g. "cheddar cheese" <isMadeFrom> "cow milk"; "beer" <isMadeFrom> "hops" (see <composedOf>);

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Belongs to category
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: To map any domain concept to any category of any classification scheme.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Afflicts
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <afflicts> Y. The disease X could adversely affect the health of an organism Y. E.g. "BSE" <afflicts> "cows".

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Great Group has Sub Order
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link Great Group to Sub Order.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has trade name, has commercial name
Is taxonomic level of
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specify that this taxonomic level apply to a concept.
X <pestOf> Y. An organism X causes harm to organism Y. E.g. "Bactrocera dorsalis" <pestOf> "Litchi chinensis".
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is a pest of
Has object of activity
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: From CWR ontology.
From CWR ontology.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has property
Is old name of, is a deprecated name for

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A concept that make use of a specific value.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Using value

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <hasPest> X. An organism Y in which the organism X causes harm. E.g. "Litchi chinensis" <hasPest> "Bactrocera dorsalis".
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has pest

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <isBeneficialFor> Y. Agent X behaves in a way that produces some result Y that is advantageous to some beneficiary. A means X through which a consequence Y can be achieved. E.g. "biological control arthropods" <isBeneficialFor> "biological control"; "pest control" <isBeneficialFor> "plant health";
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is beneficial for

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <hasSymptom> Y. A disease X presents disease characteristic Y in an organism. E.g. "BSE" <hasSymptom> "anorexia".
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has symptom
Subspecies has Species
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link Subspecies to Species.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is caused by
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <isCausedBy> X. A result Y occurred because of an agent X (animate or inanimate). E.g.: "BSE" <isCausedBy> "prions"; "water erosion" <isCausedBy> "water";

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is influenced by or Depends on

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link Great Group to Sub Group.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Great Group includes Sub Group

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link order to family.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Order includes family
Is means for
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <isMeansFor> Y. An object or process X mainly used to perform a process Y. See also <usedAs>. E.g. "curry paste grinding" <performedWithInstrument> "curry paste grinding machine"; "weapon" <instrumentFor> "killing"; "fishing pole" <instrumentFor> "fishing"; "alcohol" <instrumentFor> "cleaning"; Ploughs <isMeansFor> Ploughing ;but NOT "knives" <instrumentFor> "felling" (because knives are not primarily used for cutting down trees);
Y <indicates> X. A disease characteristic Y in an organism indicates disease X. E.g. "anorexia" <indicates> "BSE".
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Indicates
Is portion of
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <isPortionOf> X. Relation between a mass X and a piece Y taken from the mass. E.g. "cutting" <isPortionOf> "plant"; "chicken skin" <isPortionOf> "chicken"; "a slice" <isPortionOf> "a loaf of bread";
Identify the taxonomic level of a concept.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has taxonomic level
Is theme of
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: From CWR ontology.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has a related type
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: From CWR ontology.

X <isDerivedFrom> Y. A substance or product X obtained exclusively from source Y without any additional substance or product. E.g. "cow milk" <isDerivedFrom> "cow"; "plant oil" <isDerivedFrom> "plant"; "olive wood" <isDerivedFrom> "olive tree"; "chicken meat" <isDerivedFrom> "chicken"; but NOT "beer" <isDerivedFrom> "hops" (see <madeFrom>);
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is derived from
Has vector or Is host for

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <isProcessFor> Y. One or more actions, activities, methods X that produce a change or development Y. E.g.: "sterilization" <isProcessFor> "fruit cleaning".
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is process for
Object Property
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Root Property for all object properties. Introduced in order to make querying and organization of properties easier.
Link genus to species.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Genus includes species

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <includesSubprocess> Y. Process X naturally or conventionally realized at the minimum through process Y. Equivalent to <stageOf>. E.g. "milk production" <includesSubprocess> "pasteurization";
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Includes subprocess
Is subprocess of
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <isSubprocessOf> X. Y is one of one or more processes naturally or conventionally associated with the realization of process X. E.g. "pasteurization" <isSubprocessOf> "milk production";

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is spatially included in
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <isSpatiallyIncludedIn> X. Part X is an inalienable part of Y. E.g. "Congo" <isSpatiallyIncludedIn> "Africa"; "Southeast Asia" <isSpatiallyIncludedIn> "Asia"; "hand" <isSpatiallyIncludedIn> "arm".

X <isUsedAs> Y. {Taxon} X <isUsedAs> {use} Y. Use this in a plant domain. - {chemical substance} X <isUsedAs> {use} Y. Use this for chemical substance. E.g.: "apple" <isUsedAs> "fruit"; "alcohol" <isUsedAs> "cleaner"; "ddt" <isUsedAs> "pesticide";
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is used as
Sub Order includes Great Group
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link Sub Order to Great Group.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Value used in
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A measure or other value used in a specific activity or methods or for any purpose.
link species to genus.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Species has genus
Causes
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <causes> Y. Agent X (animate or inanimate) brings about a result Y. Examples: "prions" <causes> "BSE"; "water" <causes> "water erosion";
From CWR ontology.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has theme

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <surrounds> X. The object Y is physically surrounding object X. E.g., an ocean is surrounding an island. Or plasma surrounds cells. The surrounds relationship is used only for the terms that are physically immediately adjacent to each other.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Surrounds

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: From CWR ontology.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is property of
Is afflicted by
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <isAfflictedBy> X. The health of an organism Y could adversely be affected by the disease X. E.g. "cows" <isAfflictedBy> "BSE".

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is component of
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <isComponentOf> Y. An object X that is a part of a whole Y and has also an existence independently from Y. E.g. "engine part" <isComponentOf> "engine"; "leaf" <isComponentOf> "tree"; "chromosome" <isComponentOf> "cell"; but NOT "blood cell" <isComponentOf> "blood" (see <composes>).

X <affects> Y. Agent X acts on object Y in such a way that Y changes state or location. E.g. "sterilization" <affects> "bacteria"; "pest control" <affects> "pest"; "pollution of agriculture" <affects> "agriculture";
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Affects
Family has order
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link family to order.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has host or Is vector for
Is a related type of
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: From CWR ontology.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Is performed by means of
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <isPerformedByMeansOf> X. An object or process X mainly used to perform a process Y. See also <usedAs>. E.g. "curry paste grinding" <isPerformedByMeansOf> "curry paste grinding machine"; "weapon" <meansFor> "killing"; "fishing pole" <meansFor> "fishing"; "alcohol" <meansFor> "cleaning"; but NOT "knives" <meansFor> "felling" (because knives are not primarily used for cutting down trees);
Link Sub Group to Great Group.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Sub Group has Great Group

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <surroundedBy> Y. The object X is physically surrounded by object Y. E.g., an island is surrounded by ocean. Or a cell membrane is surrounded by plasma. The surroundedBy relationship is used only for the terms that are physically immediately adjacent to each other.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Surrounded by
Formerly included in
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An inclusion that was valid in the past but currently is not valid anymore.

Y <benefitsFrom> X. A result Y that is advantageous to some beneficiary, produced by the behaviour of an agent X. A consequence Y achieved through a means X. E.g. "biological control" <benefitsFrom> "biological control arthropods"; "plant health" <benefitsFrom> "pest control";
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Benefits from

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Y <hasMember> X. A social or political group Y consists of one or more subsidiary social or political units (group or individual) X. E.g. "herd" <hasMember> "cow"; "Francophone Africa" <hasMember> "Algeria", "Benin", "Burkina Faso", etc.;
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has member
Has portion
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: X <hasPortion> Y. A mass X from which a piece Y can be taken. E.g. "plant" <hasPortion> "cutting"; "chicken" <hasPortion> "chicken skin"; "a loaf of bread" <hasPortion> "a slice";
Link class to order.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Class includes order
Has scope note related to term

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: To provide a description of what can be seen on the image.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Has description

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: This property was originally called hasChangeHistory (from the traditional agrovoc thesaurus)
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Editorial note
Datatype Properties customized for the WB system.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Root Property for all datatype properties. Introduced in order to make querying and organization of properties easier.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Scope note
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Any notes for concepts or categories to clarify its use.
The source of an image is the institution, web site, etc. where the image has been taken from.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Source for the image
Has image source
Has date
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: This field can contain a date or a range of dates.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Has image name
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Each image should be assigned a name.

owl:TransitiveProperty.rdfs:comment: "Be the predecessor of" or "be earlier in time".
owl:TransitiveProperty.rdfs:label: Precedes

owl:TransitiveProperty.rdfs:comment: Relationship that is used in order to model the hierarchy of a classification scheme. A category can be in different positions in the hierarchy depending on the classification scheme you are looking at. Therefore, this relationship should not be instantiated directly to create the hierarchy, but rather a sub property specifically created for a particular classification scheme.
owl:TransitiveProperty.rdfs:label: Is sub category of
Follows
owl:TransitiveProperty.rdfs:comment: Immediately following in time or order.

owl:SymmetricProperty.rdfs:comment: Simmetric relationship indicating that two concepts are variety each other.
owl:SymmetricProperty.rdfs:label: Has variety
Causative relationship
owl:SymmetricProperty.rdfs:comment: All relationships producing an effect or being the effect of something. An expression of an agent causing or forcing a patient to perform an action (or to be in a certain condition). Functioning as an agent or cause.
Relationships linking concepts which are related in the scientifical sense in a bilogical taxonomy (e.g. species, families, etc.). To relate concepts taxonomically.
owl:SymmetricProperty.rdfs:label: Taxonomic relationship
Has related concept
owl:SymmetricProperty.rdfs:comment: The most generic relationship to relate two domain concepts. This is used if two concepts are related and none of the more speciifc relationships can be applied. It is also used for backward compatibility to thesauri, i.e. all the more specific relationships can be resolved to this relationship and will translate to the <related term> or RT thesaurus relationship.
Indicates existence in a state or capacity. Carries the meaning of a temporary state of being, often equivalent to the English "as a...".
owl:SymmetricProperty.rdfs:label: Essive relations
Instrumental relations
owl:SymmetricProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates all relationships serving or acting as a means or aid. By means of an instrument or an agent. The means whereby some act is accomplished.
All relationships involving a quantity or a measure.
owl:SymmetricProperty.rdfs:label: Quantitative relationship

owl:FunctionalProperty.rdfs:label: Taken from source
owl:FunctionalProperty.rdfs:comment: The source (website, dictionary, thesaurus, classification scheme, terminology system, etc.) where the definition has been taken from.

owl:FunctionalProperty.rdfs:label: Is preferred term.
Is a main label for this concept

owl:FunctionalProperty.rdfs:comment: This relationship is used to enter the stemmed form of term.
owl:FunctionalProperty.rdfs:label: Has stemmed form
Has ISO 3 country code
owl:FunctionalProperty.rdfs:comment: Code from the ISO standard for country names.
Values can be Project code, Conference no etc.
owl:FunctionalProperty.rdfs:label: Has number
Has code in the schema FAO Priority Area

owl:FunctionalProperty.rdfs:comment: The link to the physical image, for example the URL, where the image is available.
owl:FunctionalProperty.rdfs:label: URL link for the image
